9. What types of materials are used in automotive sunroof insulation films? Materials used include polyester films, polycarbonate, and laminated glass, which offer high insulation and durability.

10. What are the applications of automotive sunroof insulation films? These films are primarily used in automotive sunroofs for thermal insulation, noise reduction, and improved driving comfort.

